.TH "iio_dma_buffer_init" 9 "iio_dma_buffer_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
iio_dma_buffer_init \- Initialize DMA buffer queue
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" iio_dma_buffer_init
.BI "(struct iio_dma_buffer_queue *queue "  ","
.BI "struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "const struct iio_dma_buffer_ops *ops "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "queue" 12
Buffer to initialize
.IP "dev" 12
DMA device
.IP "ops" 12
DMA buffer queue callback operations
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The DMA device will be used by the queue to do DMA memory allocations. So it
should refer to the device that will perform the DMA to ensure that
allocations are done from a memory region that can be accessed by the device.
